# LotSync Architecture

LotSync is a real-time vehicle inventory and pricing sync platform for dealerships. The product is the synchronization layer—not an ESL control panel or vendor reseller platform.

**Mobile-first:** Lot operations (VIN-to-ESL pairing) happen on phones while walking the lot. Dashboard is for monitoring; mobile is the primary pairing surface.

## Monorepo

```
apps/api      — FastAPI (shared backend for all clients)
apps/web      — Next.js dashboard
apps/mobile   — React Native / Expo (future; do not scaffold until M4 validated)
packages/types, packages/api-client, packages/ui — shared client code
```

## Data Flow

```
Inventory Adapter → Normalized Vehicle → Sync Engine → Label Template Engine
  → LabelPayload → RendererAdapter → TransportAdapter → Gateway → ESL
```

## Non-Negotiable Rules

1. Do not hardcode Minew or Reynolds & Reynolds into business logic.
2. Do not assume website HTML is the source of truth; prefer the feed/API that powers the dealer website.
3. Do not build raw e-paper bitmap generation for MVP.
4. Do not bypass `RendererAdapter` or `TransportAdapter`.
5. Every dealer-owned table needs `dealership_id`.
6. VIN is the primary matching key; stock number is secondary.
7. Pairing requires VIN + ESL device identification.
8. Every critical state change must create an audit log.
9. Design all `/api/v1` endpoints mobile-compatible (JSON, lean payloads, no web-only auth).
10. Do not scaffold `apps/mobile` until pairing APIs are validated.

## Layer Ownership

LotSync owns: inventory integrations, vehicle records, VIN-to-ESL assignments, label templates, sync engine, dashboard, mobile app, shared packages, audit trail, billing.

Hardware vendors provide: e-paper screens, gateway hardware, radio transport only.

